      • SeSelector

        public SeSelector(SeSelector.SelectionParameters selectionParameters,
                  boolean keepChannelOpen,
                  SeProtocol protocolFlag)
        Instantiate a SeSelector object with the selection data, describing the selection method, the channel management after the selection and the protocol flag to possibly target a specific protocol
        Parameters:
        selectionParameters - the information data to select the SE
        keepChannelOpen - flag to tell if the logical channel should be left open at the end of the selection
        protocolFlag - flag to be compared with the protocol identified when communicating the SE

      • SeSelector

        Parameters:
        selectionParameters - the information data to select the SE
        keepChannelOpen - flag to tell if the logical channel should be left open at the end of the selection
        protocolFlag - flag to be compared with the protocol identified when communicating the SE
        extraInfo - information string (to be printed in logs)

      • setMatchingClass

        protected final void setMatchingClass(java.lang.Class<? extends MatchingSe> matchingClass)
        The matchingClass is the MatchingSe class or one of its extensions

        It is used in SeSelection to determine what kind of MatchingSe is to be instantiated. This method must be called in the classes that extend SeSelector in order to specify the expected class derived from MatchingSe in return to the selection process.

        Parameters:
        matchingClass - the expected class for this SeSelector

      • setSelectorClass

        protected final void setSelectorClass(java.lang.Class<? extends SeSelector> selectorClass)
        The selectorClass is the SeSelector class or one of its extensions

        It is used in SeSelection to determine what kind of SeSelector is to be used as argument to the matchingClass constructor. This method must be called in the classes that extend SeSelector in order to specify the expected class derived from SeSelector used as an argument to derived form of MatchingSe.

        Parameters:
        selectorClass - the argument for the constructor of the matchingClass

      • getMatchingClass
